         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
        
		
			<div n="1" type="textpart" subtype="section"><div n="a" type="textpart" subtype="fragment"><ab><lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">κ</unclear>αι<unclear reason="damage">τ</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></ab></div><div n="b" type="textpart" subtype="fragment"><ab><lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/><orig n="unresolved">ουτο</orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
			</ab></div><div n="c" type="textpart" subtype="fragment"><ab><lb n="1"/><gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/><orig n="unresolved">ο<unclear reason="damage">λ</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></ab></div></div>
		
		
			<div n="2" type="textpart" subtype="section"><div n="a" type="textpart" subtype="fragment"><ab><lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">χ</unclear>αι<unclear reason="damage">σ</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></ab></div><div n="b" type="textpart" subtype="fragment"><ab><lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/><persName key="Ampelius" type="attested"><name><orig n="unresolved">αμπ<unclear reason="damage">ε</unclear></orig></name></persName><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></ab></div><div n="c" type="textpart" subtype="fragment"><ab><lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/><orig n="unresolved">ο</orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></ab></div></div>
		
	  </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>Face 2 of b is most easily read as <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">Ἀμπε<supplied reason="lost">λιο-</supplied>
               </foreign> a reference to Ampelius. The final surviving letter might be <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">Η</foreign> rather than <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">Ε</foreign>, but the traces do not seem to suggest <foreign xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xsl:lang="grc">Ρ</foreign>, the only other real possibility.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>1.a. This too  <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </p>
            <p>2.b. <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> Ampe<supplied reason="lost">lios</supplied>
               <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>See discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="IV.21" target=".xml"/> following.</p>
            <p>For Ampelios, see also <ref type="inscription" n="38" target="040202.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="22" target="120101.xml"/>.ii and <ref type="inscription" n="43" target="020019.xml"/>.</p>
